  "description": "This morning dish leans on traditional South Indian technique but shifts the grain balance toward whole grains and lentils. Pumpkin Idli brings a distinct structure, seasoning pattern, and grain-legume balance to the table.",
  "preparation": "",
  "cooking_steps": [
    "Grease the idli moulds very lightly with oil and fill each cavity to three-quarters full.",
    "Steam over medium heat for 10 to 12 minutes until the tops look dry and a skewer comes out clean.",
    "Rest the moulds off heat for 2 minutes so the crumb firms up, then unmould with a wet spoon.",
    "Serve hot with tomato chutney; if holding for later, cool on a rack so steam does not make the idlis gummy."
  ],
